column10: This is such a dangerous intersection!!! This has been brought to the counties attention so many times.   We are playing with fire.  Elementary and middle school students use this unbelievably dangerous intersection every day without a crossing guard.
Family and I in the cross walk when a driver did not stop, I saw him reading on his cell phone and not paying attention to the road
Two cars ran red light going straight in the a.m.
Family and I in the cross walk when a driver did not stop, I saw him reading on his cell phone and not paying attention to the road

Very concerned about children crossing Patrick Henry Drive on their way to/from Cardinal Elementary. Distracted drivers are speeding down hill and have poor visibility since there’s a hill. It’s only a matter of time before someone gets hurt.
My family and I were mid-cross walk when a minivan came at a rapid rate of speed and blew through the crosswalk while we were mid-cross walk. I yelled loudly but driver never looked or slowed down.
Driver only saw me likely because I had a large umbrella and I started waving. Car stopped after crossing traffic, right next to me in the crosswalk.

This is the second car I've witnessed in one week running the red light on Washington Blvd and North McKinley.  I had the white walk crossing and already in the crosswalk when the limo decided to not stop and continue through the intersection.

My 9yo and I were crossing Washington Blvd in the crosswalk with the light when the first car rolled up to a stop, but then slowly started rolling forward into the crosswalk as we approached, before I yelled to get their attention. Driver was distracted.

the northbound bike lane on Ohio Drive continually has equipment and trailers parked in the lane, one house at the corner had a very hard to see black trailer crossing the lane and frequently blocks the lane with equipment and household items; parked vehicles
the street is narrow, car passed aggressively cutting into lead biker, car ignored the stop at the interstection
